      "<p>If the district D3 is in state S2, in which state is the district D10 in?</p>",
    ItemPassageID: 23967,
    PassageItemIndex: 0,
    Passage:
      '<p><strong>Refer to the data below and answer the questions that follow.</strong></p><p>\u00a0</p><p class="normal">D1, D2, D3, D4, D5, D6, D7, D8, D9, D10, D11 and D12 are the twelve districts in three states namely S1, S2 and S3 in a country named Taveuni. Sugarcane is produced only in these districts of Taveuni.\u00a0</p><p class="normal">The following table gives information on the total production of sugarcane in the twelve districts of Taveuni, when expressed as a percent of the total production of sugarcane in the country.</p><p class="normal"><img src="https://imsclick2cert.blob.core.windows.net/imsitemimages/636888682294321577_8542148.PNG" alt="" width="667" height="70" /></p><p class="normal">The following table gives information on the total production of sugarcane in the three states of Taveuni, when expressed as a percent of the total production of sugarcane in the country.</p><p class="normal"><img src="https://imsclick2cert.blob.core.windows.net/imsitemimages/636888682525197669_6039434.PNG" alt="" width="235" height="125" /></p><p class="normal">It is known that each state has exactly four districts out of the twelve districts mentioned. Each district can lie in only one state.\u00a0</p>',
    PassageTitle: null,
    IsLinkedQuestion: null,
    Points: 3,
    NegativePoints: 1,
    Explanation:
      '<p class="normal">It can be seen that the percent production in the twelve states are 2%, 3%, 5%, 6%, 7%, 8%, 9%, 10%, 11%, 12%, 13% and 14%.</p>\n<p class="normal">\u00a0</p>\n<p class="normal">Three districts of state S1 together have total production of 47%. The sum of 47% can be obtained using four of the given numbers as follows:</p>\n<p class="normal">1.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 14% + 12% + 11% + 10%<br /> 2.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 14% + 13% + 11% + 9%<br /> 3.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 14% + 13% + 12% + 8%</p>\n<p class="normal">\u00a0</p>\n<p class="normal">Three districts of state S3 together have total production of 18%. The sum of 18% can be obtained using four of the given numbers as follows:</p>\n<p class="normal">1.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 2% + 3% + 5% + 8%<br /> 2.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0 2% + 3% + 6% + 7%</p>\n<p class="normal">Combining these two, we get the following possibilities.</p>\n<p class="normal"><img src="https://imsclick2cert.blob.core.windows.net/imsitemimages/636888681309978144_3666196.PNG" alt="" width="638" height="248" /></p>\n<p class="normal">If D3 is in S2, possibility 3 is applicable. In that case, D10 is in state S1.</p>\n<p class="normal">Hence, [1].</p>',
