      "<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>An immiscible mixture contains three different types of liquids A, B and C. The ratio of liquids A and B is 1 : 2 and the volume of liquid C is 20 litres. 5 litres of C and 2 litres of A are replaced by equal volumes of liquid B. The ratio of liquids A and B becomes 1 : 3. Find the volume of the mixture (in litres).</p>",
