    Points: 3,
    NegativePoints: 1,
    Explanation:
      "<p>Let the initial volume of liquids A and B be x and 2x.</p>\n<p>Total volume of mixture = x + 2x + 20 = 3x + 20</p>\n<p>Final volume of liquid A = x \u2013 2</p>\n<p>Final volume of liquid B = 2x + 7</p>\n<p>Final volume of liquid C = 15</p>\n<p>Therefore, 3(x \u2013 2) = (2x + 7)</p>\n<p>Or, x = 13</p>\n<p>Volume of the mixture = 3x + 20 = 59 litres.</p>\n<p>Hence, [3].</p>",
