      "<p><span><span><span><span>In a class, there are 5 Students, A, B, C, D and E, who have to sit in a row from left to right in ascending order of their scores in a test. D and B got higher score than E and C respectively. They are also ranked according to these scores. If C got a rank better than the median rank of the class, then how many arrangements are possible?</span></span></span><br /> <!--[endif]--></span></p>",
